&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Install Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Install Manager is responsible for ensuring precise, efficient, and high‑quality installation of all cabinetry and related components in the field. Acting as the operational link between manufacturing, scheduling, logistics, and installation crews, this role ensures that projects transition smoothly from production to onsite execution. The Install Manager oversees field operations, validates jobsite readiness, directs installation teams, enforces quality standards, and resolves issues to support successful, on‑schedule project completion. This role is critical to delivering a professional installation experience and safeguarding the company’s reputation for quality craftsmanship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pre‑Install Planning &amp;amp; Verification&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review complete job packets, manufacturing staging documentation, and engineering shop drawings to ensure all required materials and components are accounted for prior to installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify jobsite readiness, including flooring installation, paint completion, drywall conditions, mechanical and appliance rough‑ins, and general site accessibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm delivery timeframe, coordinate installation scheduling, and ensure alignment between delivery logistics, jobsite conditions, and labor availability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with the Project Manager when jobsite conditions, missing prerequisites, or risk factors could impact installation success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Installation Oversight &amp;amp; Field Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and supervise installation crews, ensuring they understand scope of work, jobsite expectations, and project‑specific details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify cabinet layout accuracy, spacing, appliance openings, and alignment with approved design plans and engineering documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure installation of trim, fillers, panels, moldings, and specialty components meets company construction and aesthetic standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide real‑time field direction, adjusting workflow or sequencing as needed to maintain quality and schedule adherence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a professional, safety‑focused work environment and uphold jobsite conduct expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality Control &amp;amp; Field Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough QC walks at installation and service to verify craftsmanship, adherence to standards, and completeness of work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify issues, discrepancies, or material defects and submit SPRs (Service Part Request) with clear documentation and photos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of jobsite progress, delays, conflicts, or conditions that require PM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all field issues are documented promptly and communicated to the appropriate internal teams for corrective action.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support WO (Work Order) completion and work collaboratively to resolve outstanding items in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Knowledge&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive field installation experience with cabinetry, millwork, or construction‑related trades.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven leadership capabilities with the ability to direct crews, delegate tasks, and maintain jobsite accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem‑solving skills and the ability to make

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Starting wage is based on a number of factors including, but not limited to, the position being offered, location, education, training, and/or experience. Construction Resources offers additional competitive and non-financial benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CAD Engineer is responsible for programming equipment in order to efficiently increase and improve production of custom cabinetry to meet customers’ specific orders per business unit, including Retail, Builder, and Commercial accounts. CAD Engineers design, develop, test, and maintain tools and systems used for computer-aided design processes. Prior cabinetry experience required.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;JOB DESCRIPTION&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for producing detailed drawings ready for production approval and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet Key Performance Metrics and/or Productivity Goals as defined by the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strive to improve business performance. Constant product improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that all products produced meet Quality Standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as a dedicated team member providing fast, flexible, and excellent service to our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years’ previous Cabinet Vision experience is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the cabinetry industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail oriented with strong communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to work in a fast-paced, self-directed environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years’ experience as a Cabinet Vision Designer/Engineer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the construction industry, engineering, math, and materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in the custom cabinetry industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;WordSection1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;BENEFITS&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Medical&lt;br&gt;Dental&lt;br&gt;Vision&lt;br&gt;Employer Paid Basic Employee Life and AD&amp;amp;D Insurance&lt;br&gt;Employer Paid Long Term Disability&lt;br&gt;Flexible Spending Accounts&lt;br&gt;Voluntary&amp;nbsp;Short-Term Disability&lt;br&gt;Voluntary Life and AD&amp;amp;D Insurance&lt;br&gt;Voluntary Accident&amp;nbsp;Insurance&lt;br&gt;Voluntary Critical Illness&amp;nbsp;Insurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;EEO&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Construction Resources, our people are the driving force behind everything we do. Construction Resources is an equal opportunity employer that aspires to be the best in the business by building an associate experience that celebrates growth, development, and purpose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;PHYSICAL DEMANDS&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to speak or hear. The employee is frequently required to sit for extended periods of time, stand, walk, climb stairs, use hands to finger, handle or feel, and reach with hands and arms. Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision, distance vision, color vision, peripheral vision, depth perception and ability to adjust focus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;POSITION TYPE/EXPECTED HOURS O

&lt;p&gt;At Construction Resources and its affiliated companies, we are more than a distributor—we are a trusted partner to designers, builders, remodelers, and homeowners. For over 50 years, we’ve delivered integrated solutions that help turn ideas into reality across residential, multi-family, and commercial projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our success is built on collaboration, craftsmanship, and a commitment to excellence. Whether you contribute on the design floor, in operations, or in the field, you’ll be part of a dedicated team that values people, quality, and continuous growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our affiliated brands include Cancos, UMI/Opustone, and Bell Cabinetry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY/OBJECTIVE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join Our Team: Kitchen &amp;amp; Bath Designers Wanted&lt;br&gt;Construction Resources – Bell Cabinetry is seeking talented Kitchen and Bath Designers to help clients create beautiful and functional spaces. Ideal candidates will have the ability to design across a wide range of aesthetics, with a strong emphasis on personalization and customer satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re growing! Our newest luxury Kitchen &amp;amp; Bath showroom just opened in Westside Atlanta — a one-of-a-kind space featuring top-tier cabinetry, appliances, surfaces, and fixtures. This showroom sets a new standard in the industry and reflects our commitment to excellence and innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our primary cabinetry office and state-of-the-art manufacturing facility are conveniently located off GA 400 in Cumming, GA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re a passionate designer looking to join a dynamic and expanding team, we’d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a Kitchen Designer, you will be responsible for creating functional and aesthetically pleasing kitchen designs &amp;amp; preparing presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The designer will create and provide quotes for potential clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The designer must be proficient with designing floor plans, cabinet layout plans and facilitating the ordering process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The designer will confirm specs of appliances and hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The designer will collaborate with builders, clients, and interior designers, assisting them from sale, through the selection process, to project completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The designer will participate in showroom duties, working the occasional Saturday providing expertise to clients visiting our flagship showroom.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competencies/Skills/Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The candidate must have excellent people skills, be well-spoken, have strong organizational abilities, and the ability to multitask effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The applicant must be able to manage high end clientele with patience and professionalism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiar with the custom home construction and how cabinetry integration works within this process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The candidate must have three plus (3+) years’ kitchen and bath cabinetry experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The candidate must be experienced and proficient in sketching/drawing, PDF Expert and CAD experience is a plus. Microsoft Office proficiency is necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The applicant must have spatial intelligence, ability to read floor plans, process projects from start to finish, and be able to collaborate well with the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;WordSection1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;BENEFITS&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Medical&lt;br&gt;Dental&lt;br&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Drive your future forward with Bell Cabinetry and CR , where your role is more than just deliveries—it’s a pathway to growth. We’re looking for a dependable and safety-focused Delivery Truck Driver to join our team and play a key role in delivering high-quality materials to our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this position, you’ll operate a 26-foot straight box truck, ensuring products are loaded securely, transported safely, and placed accurately at customer sites. You’ll conduct pre-trip inspections, manage delivery documentation, and maintain a professional and courteous presence throughout each delivery. This role involves regular heavy lifting, requiring physical strength to move and place materials efficiently and safely.&amp;nbsp;We offer a competitive starting wage based on experience, along with a robust package of benefits designed to support your success and well-being.&amp;nbsp;Your dedication and performance can pave the way for a long-term career with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re a team player with a strong work ethic and a commitment to safety and customer service, we’d love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;JOB DESCRIPTION&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely operate a 26’ straight box truck.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compliance with all DOT driving regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical loading of product into designed delivery box truck.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all material is properly secured at the beginning of the shift and continuously monitor after each delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that all customer supporting paperwork is completed and returned at the end of each shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report any issues or incidents related to material damage or customer matters to the Logistics Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform the daily truck inspection, pre- and post-trip (DVIR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seeking advice and guidance on non-routine or problem areas from supervisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform and document inspections to ensure the truck and equipment are kept in good condition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of truck driving experience with a proven track record of safe driving.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possession of a Driver License (type C) – CDL license is not required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in driving automatic transmission trucks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capability to operate a lift gate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in handling commercial and residential deliveries.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to service all region’s distribution centers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20% Travel for this position.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful completion of a mandatory background check.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 points or less as shown on your Motor Vehicle Record (MVR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of DOT rules and regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of forklift experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of truck driving experience with a proven track record of safe driving.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Entry level pay rate starting at $21.00 hourly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclus

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Starting wage is based on a number of factors including, but not limited to, the position being offered, location, education, training, and/or experience. Construction Resources offers additional competitive and non-financial benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Frameless Assembler&amp;nbsp;will be responsible for the precise measurement, cutting, and installation of cabinets, glass doors, end panels, and drawer fronts, ensuring a high-quality finish that meets client specifications and industry standards. The Frameless Assembler works with a variety of materials such as glue, wood, glass, and various tools.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;JOB DESCRIPTION&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;Key Performance Indicators:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Site Inspection and Preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Material Handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adherence to Project Specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repair and Replacement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality Control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer Engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safety Compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cutting and Shaping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Installation Techniques&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pattern Alignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct on-site evaluations to measure and assess the installation area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive and inspect materials, check for defects, and ensure they meet quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acclimate materials to the installation environment, especially for products sensitive to temperature and humidity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use appropriate tools and techniques to ensure a precise and professional installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow blueprints and client specifications to achieve the desired cabinet layout and design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repair or replace damaged or worn materials as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Match existing materials and patterns to achieve a seamless look.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct quality inspections during and after installation to verify that the flooring meets industry standards and client expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promptly address defects, irregularities, or issues to ensure a high-quality finish.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with clients to understand their preferences, answer questions, and provide information on maintenance and care of the installed cabinets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to safety protocols, including the use of personal protective equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the work area is clean and free of hazards during and after installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employ appropriate installation techniques..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align patterns, seams, and transitions in accordance with the specified design, ensuring a cohesive and visually appealing result.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meticulous to ensure precise measurements and installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and craftsmanship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical fitness and ability to lift heavy materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and customer service skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience as a cabinet finisher.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with industry standards and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completion of a relevant apprenticeship program or vocational training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in the use of cutting and shaping tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to interpret installation specifications&amp;nbsp;and blueprints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in additional languages, particularly Spanish.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
