&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled CNC Machine Operator with hands-on experience in precision manufacturing environments. The ideal candidate will demonstrate strong technical expertise, attention to detail, and the ability to operate and maintain CNC equipment efficiently and safely. Proven experience operating CNC machinery, Ability to read and interpret technical drawings, blueprints, and specifications and Experience with machine setup, tool changes, and basic programming adjustments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Starting wage is based on a number of factors including, but not limited to, the position being offered, education, training, and/or experience. Construction Resources offers additional competitive and non-financial benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Machine Operator is responsible for operating several types of machinery and equipment used in the fabrication and processing of wood-based materials. This role requires technical expertise, attention to detail, and adherence to safety protocols to ensure efficient production and high-quality finished products.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;JOB DESCRIPTION&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;Key Performance Indicators:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Machine Operation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Material Handling and Preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cutting and Shaping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality Control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safety and Compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up machines, adjust settings, and load/unload materials to ensure proper operation and optimal performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor machine outputs, production rates, and material usage to meet production targets and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize machinery to cut, shape, and profile wood-based materials according to technical drawings, templates, or design specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure precise alignment, layout, and symmetry of cuts to maximize material yield and minimize waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect components for defects, imperfections, or inconsistencies in color, pattern, or finish while operating or unloading the machine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform dimensional checks, surface inspections, and quality tests to ensure compliance with project specifications and industry standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make adjustments to meet quality standards and customer expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to all safety protocols, procedures, and regulations to prevent accidents, injuries, and property damage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wear appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE) and use safety guards and devices on machinery and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine maintenance tasks on machinery and equipment to ensure optimal performance and longevity including housekeeping of machine and surrounding areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience as a CNC machine operator with knowledge of cabinet component fabrication processes, machinery, and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of material types, characteristics, and fabrication techniques, including cutting, shaping, and finishing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail, precision, and craftsmanship in working with wood-based materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physical stamina and dexterity to lift, maneuver, and work with heavy sheet goods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication skills and the ability to work independently as well as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vocational training or certification CNC machine operation.&lt;/li&gt;
